{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905475406,"sessionID":"ses_283c9a98fffehRYFFcueTbv47U","part":{"id":"prt_d7c370732001iJ1d56j73S9AVy","messageID":"msg_d7c36f25200119Qn250I5Aolvo","sessionID":"ses_283c9a98fffehRYFFcueTbv47U","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e8368e2aff3547a7ae2e911e9ea89f22","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: **Module:** docs  \n4: **Language:** TypeScript  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Initialize a Docusaurus 3.x documentation site for AgentCube, consolidating scattered design documents, specifications, and API references into a structured, searchable platform. The site provides unified navigation for architecture guides, API documentation, deployment manuals, and quick-start tutorials.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Docusaurus project initialization\n18: \n19: The system SHALL initialize a Docusaurus 3.x project with TypeScript configuration, classic preset, and standard directory structure.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Project scaffold created\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** the repository root directory exists\n24: - **WHEN** Docusaurus initialization is executed with TypeScript template\n25: - **THEN** the `docs/` directory SHALL contain `docusaurus.config.ts`, `sidebars.ts`, `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, and `src/pages/index.tsx`\n26: - **AND** the project SHALL use `@docusaurus/preset-classic` as the default preset\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: TypeScript configuration valid\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n31: - **WHEN** TypeScript compiler runs on the project\n32: - **THEN** no compilation errors SHALL occur\n33: - **AND** strict mode SHALL be enabled for type safety\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Site configuration structure\n38: \n39: The system SHALL provide a valid `docusaurus.config.ts` declaring site metadata, navigation, plugins, and theme settings.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Required config fields present\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` is parsed\n44: - **WHEN** the configuration is validated\n45: - **THEN** the config SHALL include `title`, `tagline`, `url`, `baseUrl`, `favicon`, `organizationName`, `projectName`, `themeConfig` with `navbar` and `footer`, and `presets` array\n46: - **AND** the `url` SHALL match the production deployment target\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Navbar items configured\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `themeConfig.navbar.items` is defined\n51: - **WHEN** the site renders the navigation bar\n52: - **THEN** the navbar SHALL include links to Documentation, API Reference, Architecture, Deployment, and Getting Started\n53: - **AND** each item SHALL have a `to` or `href` property pointing to valid routes\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Footer links configured\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `themeConfig.footer.links` is defined\n58: - **WHEN** the site renders the footer\n59: - **THEN** the footer SHALL include sections for Documentation, Community, and More\n60: - **AND** each link SHALL have valid `label` and `to` or `href` properties\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Sidebar structure definition\n65: \n66: The system SHALL define a `sidebars.ts` file organizing documentation into hierarchical categories.\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Sidebar categories defined\n69: \n70: - **GIVEN** `docs/sidebars.ts` is imported by the config\n71: - **WHEN** the site generates the sidebar navigation\n72: - **THEN** the sidebar SHALL include categories: `gettingStarted`, `architecture`, `api`, `deployment`, `changelog`\n73: - **AND** each category SHALL have a `label` and `items` array with document IDs\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Sidebar items resolve to documents\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** a sidebar item references document ID `getting-started/installation`\n78: - **WHEN** the user navigates to that sidebar entry\n79: - **THEN** the corresponding `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` SHALL be rendered\n80: - **AND** navigation SHALL work without broken links\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: Architecture documentation pages\n85: \n86: The system SHALL integrate existing design documents into structured architecture pages under `docs/docs/architecture/`.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Architecture overview page exists\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` is created\n91: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/architecture/overview`\n92: - **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from the repository's `design.md`\n93: - **AND** the page SHALL include system architecture diagrams using Mermaid syntax\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Sandbox orchestration page exists\n96: \n97: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/architecture/sandbox.md` is created\n98: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/architecture/sandbox`\n99: - **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`\n100: - **AND** the page SHALL explain sandbox lifecycle, session routing, and cleanup mechanisms\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Architecture pages linked in sidebar\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** the sidebar `architecture` category\n105: - **WHEN** the category is expanded\n106: - **THEN** items SHALL include `overview`, `sandbox`, `session-routing`, and `idle-cleanup`\n107: - **AND** each item SHALL correspond to a valid markdown file\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ### Requirement: API reference pages\n112: \n113: The system SHALL provide API documentation pages for Python SDK and Go client-go library.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Python SDK API page exists\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/client.md` is created\n118: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/api/sdk-python/client`\n119: - **THEN** the page SHALL document `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`, session management methods, and exception classes\n120: - **AND** the page SHALL include code examples for common usage patterns\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Client-go API page exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/api/client-go/overview.md` is created\n125: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/api/client-go/overview`\n126: - **THEN** the page SHALL document Clientset construction, CRUD interfaces, informer factory usage, and lister patterns\n127: - **AND** the page SHALL include Go code examples matching the `client-go/` implementation\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: API sidebar category structured\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** the sidebar `api` category\n132: - **WHEN** the category is expanded\n133: - **THEN** items SHALL be organized under subcategories `sdk-python` and `client-go`\n134: - **AND** each subcategory SHALL list relevant API reference documents\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Deployment guide pages\n139: \n140: The system SHALL provide deployment documentation pages covering Kubernetes configuration and Helm charts.\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment page exists\n143: \n144: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md` is created\n145: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/deployment/kubernetes`\n146: - **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from `deployment/design.md`\n147: - **AND** the page SHALL document CRD installation, namespace setup, resource requirements, and Helm values\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Helm chart parameters documented\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/deployment/helm-chart.md` is created\n152: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/deployment/helm-chart`\n153: - **THEN** the page SHALL document all configurable Helm values from `manifests/` charts\n154: - **AND** the page SHALL provide default values and recommended configurations\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Getting started tutorials\n159: \n160: The system SHALL provide quick-start documentation pages for new users.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Installation page exists\n163: \n164: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` is created\n165: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/getting-started/installation`\n166: - **THEN** the page SHALL document prerequisites (Go 1.24, Python 3.10+, Kubernetes cluster)\n167: - **AND** the page SHALL provide CLI installation commands and SDK pip install instructions\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: First sandbox tutorial exists\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox.md` is created\n172: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox`\n173: - **THEN** the page SHALL provide a step-by-step guide to create a sandbox, execute code, and retrieve results\n174: - **AND** the page SHALL include working code samples for both Python SDK and CLI\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Getting started sidebar sequence\n177: \n178: - **GIVEN** the sidebar `gettingStarted` category\n179: - **WHEN** the category is expanded\n180: - **THEN** items SHALL be ordered: `installation`, `first-sandbox`, `configuration`, `next-steps`\n181: - **AND** the sequence SHALL follow a logical learning path\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Requirement: Version and changelog pages\n186: \n187: The system SHALL provide changelog documentation integrated with GitHub Releases.\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Changelog index page exists\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** `docs/docs/changelog/index.md` is created\n192: - **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/changelog`\n193: - **THEN** the page SHALL list version releases in reverse chronological order\n194: - **AND** each release entry SHALL link to detailed changelog or GitHub Release\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Changelog sidebar configured\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** the sidebar `changelog` category\n199: - **WHEN** the category is rendered\n200: - **THEN** it SHALL link to `index` and individual version documents\n201: - **AND** documents SHALL use frontmatter `id` matching their version\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ### Requirement: Search functionality integration\n206: \n207: The system SHALL integrate search capability using Algolia DocSearch or local search plugin.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Algolia DocSearch configured\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** Algolia credentials are provided in environment\n212: - **WHEN** `themeConfig.algolia` is configured in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n213: - **THEN** the search bar SHALL appear in the navbar\n214: - **AND** search queries SHALL return indexed documentation pages\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Local search fallback\n217: \n218: - **GIVEN** Algolia credentials are not available\n219: - **WHEN** `@docusaurus/plugin-search-local` is included in plugins\n220: - **THEN** the search bar SHALL work with locally indexed content\n221: - **AND** search results SHALL be generated at build time\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ### Requirement: Multi-language support configuration\n226: \n227: The system SHALL configure i18n structure supporting English and Chinese language variants.\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: i18n directories initialized\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** i18n configuration in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n232: - **WHEN** the site is built\n233: - **THEN** `docs/i18n/zh-Hans/` directory SHALL exist for Chinese translations\n234: - **AND** `docs/i18n/en/` SHALL contain default English content\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Language switcher in navbar\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** multiple locales are configured\n239: - **WHEN** the navbar renders\n240: - **THEN** a language dropdown SHALL appear allowing locale switching\n241: - **AND** switching SHALL preserve the current page path in the target locale\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: CI/CD integration for documentation\n246: \n247: The system SHALL provide GitHub Actions workflow for automatic documentation build and deployment.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Docs workflow file exists\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/docs.yml` is created\n252: - **WHEN** changes are pushed to `docs/` directory or `main` branch\n253: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL trigger on `push` paths matching `docs/**`\n254: - **AND** the workflow SHALL use Node.js 18.x and run `npm install && npm run build`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Deployment to GitHub Pages\n257: \n258: - **GIVEN** the docs workflow completes successfully\n259: - **WHEN** the build job produces the `build/` output\n260: - **THEN** the deploy job SHALL publish to `gh-pages` branch\n261: - **AND** the site SHALL be accessible at the configured GitHub Pages URL\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Build failure notification\n264: \n265: - **GIVEN** the docs build fails due to syntax error\n266: - **WHEN** the workflow runs\n267: - **THEN** the job SHALL fail with error details\n268: - **AND** subsequent deployment SHALL be skipped\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: Homepage and custom styling\n273: \n274: The system SHALL provide a custom homepage and styling reflecting AgentCube branding.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Homepage renders correctly\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` exists\n279: - **WHEN** the user accesses the root URL\n280: - **THEN** the homepage SHALL display hero section with project title and tagline\n281: - **AND** the homepage SHALL include call-to-action buttons linking to Getting Started and Documentation\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Custom CSS applied\n284: \n285: - **GIVEN** `docs/src/css/custom.css` exists\n286: - **WHEN** the site renders\n287: - **THEN** the styles SHALL override Docusaurus defaults for colors, fonts, and spacing\n288: - **AND** the theme SHALL match AgentCube project branding guidelines\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ### Requirement: Makefile integration\n293: \n294: The system SHALL provide Makefile targets for local documentation development.\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: Docs build target exists\n297: \n298: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` is updated with docs targets\n299: - **WHEN** `make docs` is executed\n300: - **THEN** the command SHALL run `cd docs && npm run build`\n301: - **AND** the output SHALL be in `docs/build/` directory\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Docs start target exists\n304: \n305: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` is updated with docs targets\n306: - **WHEN** `make docs-start` is executed\n307: - **THEN** the command SHALL run `cd docs && npm run start`\n308: - **AND** the local development server SHALL start on port 3000\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## Constants Summary\n313: \n314: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n315: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n316: | `DOCUSAURUS_VERSION` | `3.x` | `package.json` | Docusaurus framework version |\n317: | `NODE_VERSION` | `18.x` | `.github/workflows/docs.yml` | Node.js runtime for CI |\n318: | `DEFAULT_PORT` | `3000` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Local development server port |\n319: | `BASE_URL` | `/agentcube/` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Production base path |\n320: | `SITE_URL` | `https://volcano-sh.github.io` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Production deployment URL |\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## Dependencies Summary\n325: \n326: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n327: |---------|---------|---------|\n328: | `@docusaurus/core` | `3.x` | Docusaurus core framework |\n329: | `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | `3.x` | Classic preset with blog, docs, pages |\n330: | `@docusaurus/theme-search-algolia` | `3.x` | Algolia search integration |\n331: | `@docusaurus/plugin-search-local` | `latest` | Local search fallback plugin |\n332: | `@docusaurus/module-type-aliases` | `3.x` | TypeScript type definitions |\n333: | `react` | `18.x` | React frontend framework |\n334: | `react-dom` | `18.x` | React DOM renderer |\n335: | `typescript` | `5.x` | TypeScript compiler |\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## File Changes Summary\n340: \n341: | File | Action | Description |\n342: |------|--------|-------------|\n343: | `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | create | Docusaurus configuration with site metadata, navbar, footer, plugins |\n344: | `docs/sidebars.ts` | create | Sidebar structure with categories for all documentation sections |\n345: | `docs/package.json` | create | npm dependencies and scripts for docs project |\n346: | `docs/tsconfig.json` | create | TypeScript configuration for strict mode |\n347: | `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` | create | Homepage with hero section and navigation buttons |\n348: | `docs/src/css/custom.css` | create | Custom styles overriding default theme |\n349: | `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` | create | Architecture overview derived from `design.md` |\n350: | `docs/docs/architecture/sandbox.md` | create | Sandbox orchestration documentation |\n351: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/client.md` | create | Python SDK API reference |\n352: | `docs/docs/api/client-go/overview.md` | create | Go client-go API reference |\n353: | `docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md` | create | Kubernetes deployment guide |\n354: | `docs/docs/deployment/helm-chart.md` | create | Helm chart parameters documentation |\n355: | `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` | create | Installation prerequisites and commands |\n356: | `docs/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox.md` | create | First sandbox tutorial |\n357: | `docs/docs/changelog/index.md` | create | Changelog index page |\n358: | `.github/workflows/docs.yml` | create | GitHub Actions workflow for docs CI/CD |\n359: | `README.md` | modify | Add documentation site link, simplify content |\n360: | `Makefile` | modify | Add `docs` and `docs-start` targets |\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## References\n365: \n366: - proposal.md — AR-042 detailed proposal and alternatives\n367: - project.md — AgentCube tech stack and conventions\n368: - design.md — Source for architecture documentation\n369: - deployment/design.md — Source for deployment guide\n370: - sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Source for sandbox documentation\n371: - sdk-python/ — Source for Python SDK API reference\n372: - client-go/ — Source for Go client API reference\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## Validation Checklist\n377: \n378: - [ ] Docusaurus project initialized with TypeScript template\n379: - [ ] `docusaurus.config.ts` contains all required fields\n380: - [ ] Navbar items link to valid documentation routes\n381: - [ ] Sidebar categories and items resolve correctly\n382: - [ ] Architecture pages render with Mermaid diagrams\n383: - [ ] API reference pages include working code examples\n384: - [ ] Deployment guide documents Kubernetes and Helm\n385: - [ ] Getting started pages follow logical sequence\n386: - [ ] Changelog page lists releases correctly\n387: - [ ] Search integration works (Algolia or local)\n388: - [ ] i18n directories initialized for zh-Hans\n389: - [ ] GitHub Actions workflow triggers on docs changes\n390: - [ ] Homepage renders with hero and CTA buttons\n391: - [ ] Custom CSS applies branding styles\n392: - [ ] Makefile docs targets execute successfully\n393: - [ ] Local dev server starts on port 3000\n394: - [ ] Build output in `docs/build/` is valid static site\n\n(End of file - total 394 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n**Module:** docs  \n**Language:** TypeScript  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nInitialize a Docusaurus 3.x documentation site for AgentCube, consolidating scattered design documents, specifications, and API references into a structured, searchable platform. The site provides unified navigation for architecture guides, API documentation, deployment manuals, and quick-start tutorials.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Docusaurus project initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Docusaurus 3.x project with TypeScript configuration, classic preset, and standard directory structure.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775905475380,"end":1775905475405}}}}
